1 LT Overton;

Here are some comments from two phone conversations as indicated below:

(1) Mr. Armstrong (HAAP POC) 201151RAPR26.

- sUAS detection is his chief training objective. Do not fly farther than
the "No Go" line as depicted on the NAI - Ops Graphics.
- The OPFOR is to be non-confrontational and at the main gate only. While
the staff at the main gate will be aware that an exercise will occur, the
personnel do not know where or when the exercise will happen.
- SECFOR patrolling will only physically occur outside of the perimeter
fencing and parallel to the southernmost side of US 11W.
- SECFOR patrols and screens on the interior of the facility will be
notional only.

(2) LTC Estes 202008RAPR26.

- Reviewed the NAI - Ops Graphics, RFF / RFS, and the TPFDD - Op Synch
documents.
- There will be a confirmation brief to the CG on 2 MAY 26, time TBD but
may be 1000 Hrs (local time).

Thanks for all that you are doing, Trey. I couldn't have done this at all
without you. Best regards to your wife / family, as this stuff has taken
you away from them. =F0=9F=91=8D
--=20
V/R

JOHN T. SHEAF
